Key Match Events: Ben Stokes and Chris Woakes formed an England-record stand to rescue the team from 192 for 6 to 339 for 9
Paul van Meekeren stumped by Jos Buttler (4 off 3 balls)
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed relief and delight at Ben Stokes's performance, stating Stokes takes charge whenever needed
Scott Edwards acknowledged Netherlands' recurring batting issues and stated they need to improve for their upcoming game
Miscellaneous Highlights: England snapped their five-game losing streak
Ben Stokes was named Man of the Match
Chris Woakes and David Willey dismissed O'Dowd and Ackermann early in the chase
Moeen Ali took 2 wickets for 41 runs
Adil Rashid took 3 wickets for 54 runs
Others: The pitch provided good bounce from a back of length
Netherlands struggled in the middle overs of their innings
